{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633166","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633166"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:49:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:49:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17466"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17466","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17466"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10156"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70825"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10156","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10156"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17466"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56291"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5406"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23756"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23810"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70825","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70825"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EProtective factors are characteristics or conditions that help reduce the likelihood of negative health outcomes. These can exist at individual, family, or community levels.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes how social support acts as a protective factor for health?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Provides access to healthcare services only","Reduces stress and improves coping through multiple mechanisms","Prevents exposure to infectious diseases","Increases individual wealth and resources","Eliminates genetic risk factors"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that social support \u003Cstrong\u003Ereduces stress and improves coping through multiple mechanisms\u003C/strong\u003E. Social support acts as a protective factor by providing emotional comfort, practical assistance, and informational guidance. It buffers against stress, improves immune function, and promotes positive health behaviours.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvides access to healthcare services only\u003C/strong\u003E: social networks may facilitate healthcare access, but this represents only one small component of how social support promotes health.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents exposure to infectious diseases\u003C/strong\u003E: social support does not directly prevent exposure to infections and may actually increase interpersonal contact.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases individual wealth and resources\u003C/strong\u003E: although social networks might provide some material assistance, this is not the primary mechanism through which they protect health.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEliminates genetic risk factors\u003C/strong\u003E: social support cannot alter genetic predispositions, although it may help individuals better manage genetic conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESocial support promotes health through multiple pathways including:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEmotional support and empathy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPractical help with daily tasks\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInformation sharing and advice\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMotivation for healthy behaviours\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESense of belonging and self-worth\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Social support is a key protective factor against both physical and mental illness","Strong social networks are associated with reduced mortality, better immune function, and improved mental health outcomes","Social support can be emotional (empathy, trust), instrumental (practical help), or informational (advice)"],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021.","Ostberg V, Lennartsson C. Getting by with a little help: the importance of various types of social support for health problems. Scand J Public Health. 2007;35(2):197-204. doi:10.1080/14034940600813032"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56291"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17466"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56291","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56291"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T14:19:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-06T20:31:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10156"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70825"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","posit